1 - If you sometimes wonder about the difference between arguments and parameters, a mnemonic
    with some alliteration may help: Parameters are Potential, Arguments are Actual.
    Parameters are placeholders for potential values that will be passed, and arguments are
    the actual values passed to the function.

2 - Function declarations are allowed to appear only in the program or function body.
They cannot appear in a block ( { ... } ). Blocks can only contain statements and
not function declarations. Use function expressions indeed.


https://subscription.packtpub.com/book/web_development/9781787287440/6/ch06lvl1sec32/wrapping-functions


apply(context, [arg, arg2, ..., argn])
call(context, arg1, arg2, ..., argn)

